text: Does anyone have the link to the IAA form we complete after taking a certification? I know its  in my email, but I can't find it!
It’s also on AA502 under certifications if anyone needs it in the future!

Hi Everyone, Since I am assuming most of you will have questions, I thought I would provide an update.  Update on the babe (besides being the best): GREAT suck reflex, he gobbled down his first bottle. He can be held - not skin to skin because of IVs. He is alert and has good muscle tone! He is pooping! (I never thought I'd be excited about that)! Clinically, for now he looks great. The concerning: the neurologist confirmed that he has HIE - mild to moderate brain trauma in his frontal cortex. The doctor says there is a risk for developmental issues but cannot put a number on what the probability is. Cerebral palsy ruled out for now. It's possible there are no developmental issues, and there is a potential that there is. Time will tell. Regardless of the potential issues, he is prefect and amazing and such a blessing to us already. My wife has been a total champ and is recovering well. We are still processing all of this but are grateful for the progress he has made. Thanks all for your love and support. I saw that many of you signed up for the meal train. Thank you so very much.
Got the fishbowl in Hunt if anyone is studying and needs more quiet than the grad lounge  :slightly_smiling_face:

text: Let's do our best to keep the flu out of the Institute!  I'm going to get a flu shot on Oct. 20 in EB II (On centennial campus close to school)  between the M&T Bank info session and the Women in Analytics panel on Thursday and would love some company.  We just need our insurance cards or they'll charge $25 to your student account.   Here's the link to other on campus times if anyone is interested but can't go Thursday:  <https://healthypack.dasa.ncsu.edu/care-provided/flu-vaccinations/>
<@U1L4RTKCM> is this only if you have student insurance?

I think a lot of insurance works.  This is what the email says:   Student Health Services accepts the following insurance plans: Blue Cross Blue Shield, Cigna, Student Blue and Tricare. Students with other insurance plans will have $25.00 charged to their university student account.
I don't know if anyone has allergies, etc but the flu shot is can contain egg related proteins because of the way it is made so if u r allergic to eggs you CANNOT take the shot!
Actually, you still can take the shot with egg allergies (according to CDC), you should just do it at a doctors office where they can monitor and help if you have a reaction.
My doctor told me to avoid it all costs but that's probably because my reactions are through the roof.
